Wizard Ghost: Hello, dear mortal!
Wizard Ghost: It is I, Emrys - Unfortunately, it seems I have run out of lessons to teach you, and thus, we have reached the end of your apprenticeship.
Wizard Ghost: I have known you for a short time, but I truly believe you are the most gifted apprentice I could ever have taken on.
Wizard Ghost: And truly, I am thankful that I have finally met someone willing to place their trust in me, and my sorcery - Thank you.
Wizard Ghost: I hope, above all else, that you are finding fulfillment, brewing coffee for us ghosts.
Wizard Ghost: Is that what you desired in life, too? Or is it a new journey? Ah, no matter - I trust you to continue what makes you happy.
Wizard Ghost: As for myself, well... Ever since our last session, I have been deep in thought.
Wizard Ghost: And now, I have decided to swear off necromancy. Our lesson made me realize that perhaps, I have been holding too tightly onto regrets from a life bygone, despite becoming what I so desperately wanted to be back then.
Wizard Ghost: I, Emrys Alistair Artemis Evander - <wiggle>perhaps I should shorten some of my names</wiggle> - am a wizard, and I am in control over my own destiny!
<<reset>>
Wizard Ghost: Now, I shall continue my journey to discover all of this realm's secrets, and share the joys of magic with every soul I can find!
Wizard Ghost: And perhaps, once I learn enough, I can return to this humble cafe, and teach you all I know once again, dear mortal.
Wizard Ghost: I admit, I will miss our talks of sorcery over coffee for as long as we are separated.
Wizard Ghost: But this is not goodbye - In fact, this is only the start of our journey!
Wizard Ghost: So, until next time, my dear mortal - Take care of yourself, and remember that the great Emrys will always be watching over you.
